    "In theory, this method only has a high degree of overlap, the better the effect, but it produces a lot of redundancy.",
    "In addition, the convolution kernel of standard C3D used by SCNN is 3, and the receptive field is too small, so only short time-sequence information can be used.",
    "Considering the limitations of the sliding window method, Gao et al. (2017a) proposed in 2017 that the TURN model could reduce the amount of computation and improve accuracy.",
    "The main idea of this model is to draw on the boundary regression in Faster-RCNN (Ren et al. 2015).",
    "As shown in Fig. 27, the video should first be divided into fixed-size units, such as 16 video frames, and each group should learn one feature (using C3D)."
